<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Should Strive to Further Improve Export Structure: Vice-Trade Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 16 (Xinhua) -- China wants to accelerate
improvements in the structure of its exports in a bid to increase
its competitive ability in international markets, according to Sun
Zhenyu, vice-minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
today.
</P>
<P>
Sun told a seminar on international market strategies here that
China has adopted some policies over recent years to support and
encourage high and new technologies.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, China's technical exports with high added
value merely accounted for 5.3 percent of the total exports in
1997 and the country's traditional textiles and hardware could
hardly cope with the world market demand.
</P>
<P>
China should try hard to increase the scale of highly technical
products, improve the quality of traditional export goods, and
develop more brand-name products, Sun said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
