<HEADLINE> Istanbul Stock Exchange Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Istanbul Stock
Exchange National-100 Index closed at 1,990.73 on Friday, up 5.37
points, or 0.29 percent, from Thursday's finish.
</P>
<P>
The trading was heavy with the turnover reaching over 61
trillion Turkish Liras (over 221 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The financial index rose 6.75 points, or 0.32 percent, to
close at 2,427.96 points, the service index went up 63.07
points, or 2.30 percent, to close at 2,784.29 points, and the
industrial index fell 7.19 points, or 0.43 percent, to close at
1,630.59 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
