<HEADLINE> Pak PM Announces release of All Detained Indian Fishermen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif Friday unilaterally announced unilateral release of
all Indian fishermen and boats in Pakistan's custody.
</P>
<P>
He conveyed this decision to Indian Foreign Secretary K.
Ragunath who called on him Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
"As a gesture of goodwill and in view of humanitarian
consideration, the prime minister conveyed his decision to
unilaterally release all Indian fishermen and boats in Pakistan's
custody," said an official statement issued after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister underscored the importance of strengthening
peace and security and emphasized its linkage with peaceful
resolution of all outstanding issues including the core issue of
Jammu and Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
"A just settlement of the Jammu and Kashmir dispute will pave
the way to increase cooperation between the two countries," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the economic and social welfare of the peoples
of Pakistan and India was a matter of prime concern and urgent
priority.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said that the two countries should agree on
a nuclear and conventional stabilization regime which would
contribute to reduction of tensions and avoidance of conflicts.
</P>
<P>
Ragunath said that the Indian delegation to the current foreign
secretary level talks was mandated to discuss issue of peace and
security and Jammu and Kashmir with a positive approach.
</P>
<P>
He said that India desired to increase cooperation with
Pakistan across the board which would in due course lead to
resolution of difficult issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
