<HEADLINE> UK to Urge Kosovo Albanians to Support New Kosovo Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 16 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook is to urge ethnic Albanians in Kosovo to back a new agreement
designed to end the current Kosovo crisis, according to British
government sources.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic Kosovo Albanians have so far refused to support the
Kosovo agreement reached between U.S. envoy Richard Holbrooke and
Yuogoslav President Slobodan Milosevic, insisting on total
independence of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
A British government official told reporters Friday that the
new Kosovo deal "is a good and promising agreement and the key now
is to make it work. The agreement needs the support of the Kosovo
Albanians and that's what we expect of them."
</P>
<P>
Cook is expected to hold informal talks next with a Kosovo
Albanian delegation led by Fehmi Agani, the Kosovars' chief peace
negotiator during a visit to Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
"We hope the meeting is one where we agree to take forwards the
Holbrooke agreement and not one where we argue about
independence," the official said.
</P>
<P>
The official also made it clear that the Kosovo Liberation Army
should not try to take advantage of the deal by moving into areas
vacated by security forces.
</P>
<P>
Cook is also due to visit Bulgaria and Romania next week to
assure them of Britain's continued political support and to
encourage them to press ahead with reforms which would increase
their chances of joining the European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
