<DOCNO> XIE19981017.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> XNBA Legends Beaten by China National Squad 96-98 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The "Sky Hook" Kareem
Abdul-Jabbar hit seven points and All-Star MVP Tom Chambers
scored 17 in a close defeat of 96-98 to their much younger
Chinese rivals in the first stop of a four-game Thakral American
XNBA legends China '98 here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 51-year-old Abdul-Jabbarm, who played for 9 minutes 34
seconds also with two rebounds, and his former NBA stars
teammates of over 40 in an averaged age, really shocked their
Chinese counterparts, averaged in 26, at the thrilling battle
which the NBA legends might had won if Adrian Dantley's
three-pointer on the buzzer could go through the net.
</P>
<P>
Coached by Basketball Hall of Fame Oscar "The Big O"
Robertson, the XNBA Legends will play the Chinese National team
again on Sunday and move to Hefei of Anhui Province and Beijing
for their third and fourth games on October 18 and 23.
</P>
<P>
With younger legs and accurater long shots, Asian Games
champion China led 59-56 at the interval and the XNBAers took
over the lead 62-61 midway in the third quarter with their strong
inside games.
</P>
<P>
The two sides tied four times in the last two minutes and
China want ahead 98-96 with tow free-throws from Zhang Jinsong,
just 46 second to go on the clock.
</P>
<P>
Jay Humphries missed the next jumper but he stole the ball
from China's guard Li Xiaoyong and passed it to Dantley, who
tossed the shot just before the buzzer some 12 meters (35 feet)
away and it bounced on the rim a several times before sliding
aside.
</P>
<P>
Dantley and former NBA scores title winner Alex English each
added 10 points for the XNBA stars while forward Zhang Jinsong
hit a game high 33 points, included six three-pointers, for host
China, who is taking the event as the last warm-up chances before
to defend their title at the Asian Games in Thailand in the
coming up December.
</P>
<P>
The XNBA legends also include NBA top 50 player Moses Malone,
who will arrived in Shanghai on Saturday and play the Sunday
game, Walter Davis, Alton Lister, Kiki Vandeweghe, Darnell
Valentine, Lazarus Sims and Frank Brickowski, all of them had
played and scored on Friday's first game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
