<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lewis Poised To Sign For Unification Showdown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Britain's WBC heavyweight
champion Lennox Lewis is ready to put pen to paper for his
multi-million heavyweight unification fight against Evander
Holyfield on February 27 or March 6.
</P>
<P>
Lennox's promoter Panos Eliades said, "Now Holyfield's signed,
there's no problem with Lennox signing, which will probably be
done on Monday. I've spoken to Holyfield's lawyer Jim Thomas and
everything looks good."
</P>
<P>
Lennox is waiting to see if the television deal, which is
being negotiated by American promoter Don King, is completed with
cable network Home Box Office.
</P>
<P>
A TV hitch has still to be ironed out -- not over Lewis v
Holyfield itself but on Holyfield's future fights if he beats
Lewis.
</P>
<P>
HBO wants to sign up the WBA and IBF champion Holyfield if he
becomes the undisputed champion, as do their pay-per-view rivals
Showtime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
