<HEADLINE> Angola Issues Micro-Credit to Help Women </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 16 (Xinhua) --The Angolan government has
decided to grant micro-credit for women in the coffee-growing
area.
</P>
<P>
The the Secretariat of State of Coffee said in a document
reaching here Friday that the loan is aimed at helping improve
living level of the women in coffee-growing areas, diversify
their production and encourage them to receive various training,
so that they can become independent economically.
</P>
<P>
Each woman could get a sum of 690 U.S. Dollars for one or two
agricultural projcts like cattle raising, vegetable planting.
</P>
<P>
The money is to be due in three years.
</P>
<P>
Women farmers could learn some technology and increase their
family income, and at the same time add more supply to the
market, the document said.
</P>
<P>
About 10,000 women farmers are to be benefited in northern
Angola's Uige Province, where the loan is to be launched in a
trial issue. The money for the loan has come from public and
private financial institutions in Angola and some
non-governmental organizations abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
