<HEADLINE> Russia, Belarus Join Hands Against NATO Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Defense ministers from Russia
and Belarus vowed here Friday to join hands against the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization's eastward expansion.
</P>
<P>
Russian Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev and his Belarussian
counterpart, Alexander Chubakov, said after the admission of the
Czech Republic, Hungary and Poland, "NATO borders come 750
kilometers closer to Russia and Belarus."
</P>
<P>
"The area of NATO-controlled interests has approached our
borders significantly," Sergeyev said.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the two defense ministries had worked out
specific measures to resist the enlargement but refused to give
any details, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Chubakov, for his part, said Belarussian armed forces will
become the first echelon of the joint defense of Russia and
Belarus against NATO.
</P>
<P>
The two defense chiefs also discussed Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"The irreversible process of a peace settlement" has begun in
Yugoslavia, Sergeyev told reporters after a joint session of the
Russian and Belarussian defense ministries.
</P>
<P>
"We fully control the situation (in Kosovo), closely follow its
development, hope that it will be settled by peaceful means and
reason will prevail," Sergeyev said. "Russia has done quite a
lot." 
</P>
</TEXT>
