<HEADLINE> S. African Banks Fine-Tune Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 16 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's major
commercial banks Friday fine-tuned their prime lending and
mortgage rates after the central bank lowered its repo rate
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
First National Bank (FNB), Standard Bank and ABSA announced
that they would drop their prime rates by one percentage point to
24.5 percent with effect next Monday.
</P>
<P>
Standard Bank and ABSA will also cut their mortgage rates by
one percentage point and 0.5 percentage point respectively. FNB's
mortgage rate will remain unchanged at 24 percent.
</P>
<P>
The banks' move came after the Reserve Bank, the central bank
of South Africa, lowered its repo rate by 0.25 percentage point
to 21.6 percent Wednesday amid improved market conditions and the
steady rally of the Rand.
</P>
<P>
The repo rate is the rate at which the central bank lends to
the commercial banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
