<HEADLINE> More ARATS, SEF Exchanges Are Expected (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Chen Yunlin, director of the
State Council's Taiwan Affairs Office, who spoke at a banquet in
Beijing's Great Hall of the People in honor of Koo Chen-fu and his
party here today, said that he expects the mainland's ARATS and
Taiwan's SEF to start talks on procedural matters of political
negotiation as soon as possible and to follow this with a
re-opening of talks on practical and economic issues.
</P>
<P>
Chen said the mainland always supports continued contacts and
exchanges between ARATS and SEF for the benefit of peaceful
reunification and dialog on developing relations across the Taiwan
Straits and expects the two to achieve something by this.
</P>
<P>
The mainland and Taiwan have been separated for almost 50 years
and this is unfortunate for the Chinese nation, Chen noted. But he
added that there has been an increase in the economic and trade
relations across the straits, an interflow of personnel and other
exchanges thanks to the joint efforts of compatriots living on
both sides and the departments concerned in the past decade and
more.
</P>
<P>
At present, the cross-straits relations are now facing new
opportunities and challenges at the turn of the century, Chen
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
