<HEADLINE> More ARATS, SEF Exchanges Are Expected (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chen said that Koo's mainland trip is the outcome of
increased exchanges and cooperation between ARATS and SEF, so it
is important that ARATS-SEF dialogues be increased and relations
across the Taiwan Straits further improved.
</P>
<P>
ARATS President Wang Daohan met with Koo in Shanghai to discuss
issues of common and respective concern, Chen said, and that he
appreciates the consensus reached between ARATS and SEF on four
points, including common ground in conducting multi-field and
multi-form dialog in politics, economics and other spheres.
</P>
<P>
Koo said he was impressed by the fact that his visit is a rare
chance for the starting point of interaction between ARATS and SEF
that allows both to exchange views and fully communicate their
concepts and views concerning problems in developing cross-straits
relations. He expressed his belief that his visit will
lay the basis for mutual trust.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the banquet, Chen presented Koo with an antithetical
couplet inferring renewal of brotherhood after ordeals and ensuing
sufferings written by Qi Gong, a well-known Chinese calligrapher.
</P>
<P>
In return, Koo sent a gift to Chen, and Koo's wife Yen Cho-yun
exchanged gifts with Chen's wife Lai Xiaohua.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the banquet were Tang Shubei, executive
vice-president of ARATS, and Wang Yonghai, deputy director of the
State Council's Taiwan Affairs Office.
</P>
<P>
The banquet is followed by a traditional Beijing Opera
performance hosted by ARATS in Koo's honor this evening at the
Chang'an Grand Theater in downtown Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Koo was in such high spirits that he ascended the stage and
sang an episode of a very popular traditional Peking drama, which
brought the evening performance to its climax.
</P>
<P>
Yu Shihai, a well-known Chinese Peking Opera master, praised
Koo's opera singing as superb and full of feelings.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yunlin, Tang Shubei, Wang Yonghai and their wives were
among those present at the performance.  
</P>
