<HEADLINE> NBA Star Drexler Welcomed As Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Clyde Drexler has yet to
coach his first game at the University of Houston, but already 16
of the 28 shiny boxes are sold out for the next three years at
Hofheinz Pavilion, and most of the 8,600 season tickets available
also are gone.
</P>
<P>
"We've gone to the records, and looking back at the Phi Slamma
Jamma days, we are right there," AD Chet Gladchuk said. "We're
down to 500 tickets and we are sold out for the season."
</P>
<P>
Drexler ended his NBA Hall of Fame career with the Houston
Rockets last season and returned to the school where he was a
member of the Phi Slamma Jamma dunking crew that went to the NCAA
Final Four three straight years in the 1980s, two with Drexler on
the team.
</P>
<P>
Season ticket sales started a dramatic increase on March 18
when Drexler was named coach. After averaging 2,838 at 13 home
games last season, the Cougars will play before nearly sold-out
home crowds this season.
</P>
<P>
"We've been wanting that type of crowd and Clyde is bringing
in a lot of people," said Chad Hendrick, a sophomore who started
22 games last season. "We can't do anything but win games now. We
want to show Houston that we can win."  
</P>
</TEXT>
