<HEADLINE> Three French Warships Arrive in Qatar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Three French warships arrived
in Qatar Saturday to take part in Franco-Qatari war games
codenamed "Gilbot 982" due to start on Wednesday, according to
reports reaching here from Doha.
</P>
<P>
The three French warships - a supply and flagship, a frigate,
and an amphibian operation ship - were carrying 600 servicemen on
board, informed sources in Doha said.
</P>
<P>
The warships will take part in the two-day military exercises
along with the Qatari army forces, air force, and navy.
</P>
<P>
The exercises are part of a joint defense pact signed by the
two countries in 1994. Their last joint exercises took place in
March this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
