patience, dedication and fortitude, would be able to recover the
losses by completing the reconstruction and rehabilitation
programs.
</P>
<P>
The government has taken immediate, short-term and long-term
programs for post-flood rehabilitation and reconstruction, she
told the nation.
</P>
<P>
Proper steps would be taken to manage the country's water
bodies to make the best utilization of surface water as well as to
protect ecological balance by planting more trees and protecting
forest resources, she stated.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the rivers would be properly managed through necessary
dredging which would help increase the water-containing capacity
as well as ensure safe and proper navigation, she added.
</P>
<P>
The government had given top priority to food security of the
people, and to meet of an estimated 4.3 million tons deficit,
necessary steps have been taken by the authorities, she said.
</P>
<P>
She said that by this time, 0.9 million tons of foodgrains have
been imported by the government, 1.5 million tons by the private
sector, 1.5 million tons were received from foreign countries as
annual food aid, while another 625,000 tons are still in
government stock.
</P>
<P>
Since floods started in mid-July, the government set up 4,732
medical teams which worked round-the-clock in the flood-hit areas,
she said, adding that 107 temporary medicare centers were opened
during the calamity and in addition to those, special measures
have been taken to check diarrhea and other water-borne diseases.
</P>
