<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique Denies Foreign Wastes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Prime Minister
Pascoal Mocumbi has opposed the importation of wastes from
abroad, saying that his government does not authorize any firm to
import and handle foreign wastes in the country.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister made the remarks in Maputo Friday.
</P>
<P>
Previously, there were reports saying that the Mozambican
International Waste Group had been authorized to import and
dispose foreign waste in the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's Noticias quoted Mocumbi as saying that it is
necessary to check if the firm had had the authorization.
</P>
<P>
If the firm did win the authorization from the Mozambican
government, then the government had gone against its commitment
to the related international treaties, said the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
"I don't believe any firm would have been authorized to import
and dispose foreign waste in the territory of Mozambique," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the handling of wastes created in Mozambique,
Mocumbi stressed the necessity to take measures to ensure that
wastes created in Mozambique can be properly handled in line with
the international treaties and without any harm to the human
being and other living things.
</P>
<P>
But he said: "No import of any poisonous waste should be
allowed." "Anyone who wants to start a firm involving in foreign
waste disposal should give up the idea because no authorization
would be issued," he added.
</P>
<P>
He noted that either Mozambicans or foreigners are free to
raise their investment plans.
</P>
<P>
If they want to invest in the disposal of the local wastes,
they will surely be welcomed.
</P>
<P>
But, the prime minister stressed, if they want to deal with
imported wastes, their investment plans would certainly be denied.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said that in a document of approval issued on
February 15, 1996, the Mozambican Ministry of Coordination for
Environmental Affairs had authorized the Mozambican International
Waste Group to exclusively deal with the import, export and
disposal of various wastes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
