<DOCNO> XIE19981017.0108 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fifth Asian Dermatology Congress Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Today was the last day of the
Fifth Asian Dermatology Congress, whose theme was "Oriental
Medicine And The World".
</P>
<P>
Stephen Katz, chairman of the World Federation of Dermatology,
was present along with doctors from many countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
About 700 research papers were sent to the congress, whose
purpose is to promote academic exchanges and discuss the latest
developments in dermatology. The topics included basic science in
dermatology, autoimmune skin disorders, psoriasis, skin neoplasm,
sexually transmitted diseases, oriental medicine, and cosmetic
dermatology.
</P>
<P>
There was also a course on general concepts in traditional
Chinese medicine and oriental medicine applications to dermatology.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Dermatology Association, which was founded in 1989 in
Hong Kong, holds a congress every three years. Its fifth congress
was organized by the Chinese Society of Dermatology.
</P>
<P>
Many famous companies displayed medicines, medical equipment,
and cosmetic products during the congress.  
</P>
</TEXT>
