<HEADLINE> Maradona To Launch Drug Counterattack For Being Wronged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 17 (Xinhua)-- Controversial soccer star Diego
Maradona could soon file a suit against the Italian Football
Federation following a revelation that his 15-month suspension in
1991 had resulted from a botched dope test.
</P>
<P>
Maradona was banned following a positive test for cocaine
after a league match for Napoli against Bari, which marked the
end of his sensational career.
</P>
<P>
But a report by ANSA news agency claims that blunders with the
equipment were made in March 1991 at the now discredited Acqua
Acetosa test laboratory, currently at the center of a drugs
scandal in Italian soccer.
</P>
<P>
Not only Maradona's sample, but also the supposedly 'clean'
control sample, which is only used for comparison purposes to
make sure the equipment is set-up correctly, also showed traces
of cocaine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
