<HEADLINE> Koo Chen-fu Palace Museum Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Koo Chen-fu, chairman of
Taiwan's Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF), and members of his
party visited the Palace Museum this afternoon in the company of
Liu Gangqi, deputy secretary general of the Association for
Relations Across the Taiwan Strait (ARATS).
</P>
<P>
The Palace Museum, served as the imperial palace of the Ming
(1368-1644) and Qing (1644-1911) dynasties.
</P>
<P>
In front of the Tai He Dian (Hall of Supreme Harmony), Koo took
a group photo with his wife Yen Cho-yun and other delegation
members.
</P>
<P>
They then visited the Zhong He Dian (Hall of Complete Harmony),
the Bao He Dian (Hall of Preserving Harmony), and Yu Hua Yuan
(Imperial Garden).  
