<HEADLINE> India's Foreign Exchange Reserves Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- India's foreign currency
assets increased by 282 million U.S. dollars to 26.466 billion
dollars till October 9, and as a result, its total foreign
exchange reserves reached 29.465 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the weekly Statistical Supplement published by the
Reserve Bank of India Saturday, the foreign currency assets is 491
million dollars more than the end-March level while the total
reserves are higher by 98 million dollars over the same period.
</P>
<P>
Since the December 1997, accretion to foreign currency assets
has been to the extent of 2.501 billion dollars, the weekly
periodical said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
