<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interest Rate in Macao Turned Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Following interest rate cuts in
the United States and Hong Kong, the Macao Association of Banks
has announced that interest rate in Macao will be tuned down 0.25
percent beginning from Next Monday.
</P>
<P>
Some business people in Macao expressed their disappointment
about the slight cut of banking rate, but they believe the trend
of rate decrease will help reduce cost in industrial, commercial
and real estate sectors and revitalize the local economy.
</P>
<P>
Many estimate that there will be more interest rate cuts in the
near future.
</P>
<P>
Real estate proprietors think a lower banking rate will be
conducive to reinvigorate housing business. In addition, the good
news is that real estate sector in Hong Kong is showing signs of
recovery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
