<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pichit Retains WBA Junior Flyweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Thai boxing champion Pichit
Chor-Siriwat returned his junior flyweight title of the World
Boxing Association (WBA) here Saturday after the referee stopped
a match against South Korean contender Lee Tae-Kil in the eighth r
ound.
</P>
<P>
Pichit dominated the fight from start to finish with powerful
left and right hooks to the face and occasional blows to the
body, and opening a cut above Lee's right eyebrow in the second
round.
</P>
<P>
The ring doctor advised the referee to stop the fight in the
eighth and Pichit was declared match winner by technical knockout.
</P>
<P>
Pichit improved his fight record to 19 wins, one draw and one
loss, while Lee Tae-Kil's record now stands at 16 wins, 2 draws
and 2 losses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
