<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Killed in Plane Crash in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- A twin-engine plane crashed
Saturday in a mountainous village in the southern Philippines,
killing one and injuring three others.
</P>
<P>
Police said the five-seat small plane plunged into the village
of Kalilangan, Iligan city, Lanao del Sur province, reportedly due
to bad weather.
</P>
<P>
One woman passenger was confirmed killed while the pilot and
two other passengers wounded in the accident. The wounded have
been sent to a nearby hospital, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
