<HEADLINE> Rios To Meet Woodforde In Singapore Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 17 (Xinhua)-- World number three Marcelo
Rios of Chile and Australian doubles specialist Mark Woodforde
both advanced into the final on Saturday at the 700,000 U.S.
dollars Singapore Open.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Rios always had the upper hand in a clash of
forehands, moving Jim Courier around the court before he hammered
the former number one American 6-2 6-1 to make the final.
</P>
<P>
While Woodforde, 33, had to rally back to hold off Dutchman
Sjeng Schalken, ranked 80th, 0-6,6-4,6-2 after a calamitous start.
</P>
<P>
The final between the two finalists on Sunday is expected to
be an intriguing clash. Woodforde, 10 years older than his
high-flying opponent, had beaten second seeded Croat Ivanisevic
and Denmark's Kenneth Carlsen in previous rounds although it is
four years since he last appeared in a singles final. 
