<DOCNO> XIE19981017.0140 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Agency Helps Uganda to Eradicate Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The International Fund for
Agricultural Development (IFAD) has helped Uganda achieve much in
eradication of poverty and pledged to contribute more toward this
end.
</P>
<P>
IFAD President Fawzi H. Al-Sultan, who is on a five-day visit
to Uganda, made this promise in a press release issued Saturday
morning.
</P>
<P>
"Since 1981 IFAD has been a partner in Uganda's development by
financing nine projects, bringing total investments in the
country to approximately 150 million U.S. Dollars," said the
press release.
</P>
<P>
At present, the IFAD has shifted from assisting basic rural
rehabilitation toward the re-emergence of the Ugandan small
farmers.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Rome-based agency has taken the initiative of
reducing Uganda's debt within the framework of its participation
in the Heavily-Indebted Poor Countries (HIPC) Debt Initiative.
</P>
<P>
On May 26, 1998, the IFAD and the Ugandan government signed an
agreement for 20 million U.S. Dollars to finance a vegetable oil
development project which aims at revitalizing and increasing
domestic vegetable oil production in the east African country,
thereby lessening its dependence on imports.
</P>
<P>
The IFAD president acknowledged that from the early years of
this decade, Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni has expressed his deep
concern on the priority of reducing poverty.
</P>
<P>
While special days such as the International Day for the
Eradication of Poverty come and go, the only way to eradicate
hunger and poverty is to persistently work at it each day, he
said.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the world's poorest and through the United
Nations, the IFAD regards the 17th of October as the day to
rededicate efforts for and with the rural poor, the press release
added.
</P>
<P>
The IFAD president is scheduled to attend celebrations in
southwestern Mubende District Saturday to mark the special day.
The celebrations in Uganda reflect a long and solid development
partnership between the IFAD and the Ugandan government.
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, there are still 800 million
people around the world who are unable to meet their basic needs
on a sustainable basis and 70 percent of them are the rural poor.
</P>
<P>
The IFAD was created in 1978 by the United Nations as a
specialized agency to give exclusive attention to the eradication
of hunger and poverty.
</P>
<P>
The International Day for Eradication of Poverty, observed by
the U.N. on October 17 since 1993, provides an occasion for all
citizens of the world to join in solidarity with those most in
need. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
