<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With Hong Kong Chief Executive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in a
meeting today with the Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa, said that the Central
Government will unswervingly implement the principle of "one
country, two systems", and will not interfere in affairs within
HKSAR's self-governing.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that practice over the past year since the
establishment of the HKSAR has shown that Hong Kong people can
administer Hong Kong well, and said that the Central Government
will, as always, support work of the HKSAR government led by
Mr. Tung Chee Hwa.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that the Basic Law of the HKSAR is a
fundamental law of the HKSAR, calling on all social circles to act
in accordance with the law and safeguard the authoritativeness of
the law, and to administer Hong Kong according to the law.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Central Government firmly supports the HKSAR
in pursuing "Hong Kong people administering Hong Kong" and a high
degree of autonomy in accordance with the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also expressed his hope that people from all social
circles in Hong Kong will unite together under the banner of
loving the motherland and Hong Kong, and work with the HKSAR
Government, to overcome current temporary economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Tung is here to report on his work to the Central Government.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, Zeng Qinghong, director of the
General Office of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), and Liao Hui, director of the Hong Kong and Macao
Affairs Office of the State Council, were present during the
meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
