<HEADLINE> Bone Marrow Transplant Patient Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Zhu Guangfu, a sixth-grade
primary school pupil in Haikou, capital of the southern island
province of Hainan, recently died of rejection symptom following a
bone marrow transplant.
</P>
<P>
Surgeons who performed the complicated operation on September
16 attributed the boy's death to the acute rejection symptom
resulting from the bone marrow transplant and his extremely low
immunity level.
</P>
<P>
Zhu had been in a relatively stable condition before October
10, but after that he had been listed in critical condition with
high fever and chills.
</P>
<P>
Zhu had been suffering from leukemia for two years. As no
suitable marrow donor was found among his relatives, he awaited
surgery at Hainan People's Hospital until a teacher in Taiwan was
found with suitable marrow among the 300,000 volunteers at a
marrow-donation bank in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Zhu's case, there have been only four cases of
non-blood-relationship marrow transplants in the Chinese mainland
and two of them were successful.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
