<HEADLINE> Koo Chen-fu Continues His Tour in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Koo Chen-fu, chairman of the
Taiwan-based Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF), continued his tour
in Beijing this morning after his arrival on Friday.
</P>
<P>
At around 9 a.m., Koo, his wife Yen Cho-yun and other members
of his party paid a visit to the Memorial Hall of Dr. Sun Yet-sen
in the Biyun Temple, located on the Fragrant Hills in western
Beijing suburbs.
</P>
<P>
Koo presented a basket of flowers to and all the members of the
delegation made three bows in front of the statue of Sun Yat-sen.
</P>
<P>
Koo expressed his willingness to promote exchanges between the
two sides of the Taiwan Straits, bringing into practice the
thought and spirit of Dr. Sun Yat-sen.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to the famous Beijing University later this
morning, Koo expressed his hope that the universities on both
sides of the Taiwan Straits will strengthen and deepen exchanges
and cooperation, to set an example for the cross-straits
exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Koo and his party toured around the campus of the university,
visited its new library and laid flowers in front of the bronze
statue of Mr. Yan Fu, a celebrated educationist and ideologist and
the first president of the University.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University, originating from the Metropolitan
University (Jingshidaxuetang) founded in 1898, is the first
national university in modern China, and got its current name in
1912. Over the past 100 years, the university has trained 190,000
talents in various fields. 
</P>
