<HEADLINE> Cambodian Government to Form Green Trade Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian government is to
form the Green Trade Import-Export Company, aimed to oversee the
import and export of agricultural products, seeds and fertilizer,
according to Cambodia Daily Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was adopted at a cabinet meeting attended by
Second Prime Minister Hun Sen and First Prime Minister Ung Hout.
</P>
<P>
Undersecretary of State for Information Sieng Lapresse said the
company, to be called Green Trade, is to monitor the quality in
such products as fertilizer, increase agricultural yields and
standardize food production.
</P>
<P>
The company will be financially and administratively
independent, under the jurisdiction of the ministries of Finance
and Commerce.
</P>
<P>
Sieng Lapresse said the company will be crucial in identifying
quality produce and assessing environmental standards of
fertilizer.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture employs technicians to analyze
samples of imported fertilizer before it is brought into the
country. 
</P>
