<HEADLINE> Overweight Boy Receives Acupuncture Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 17 (Xinhua) -- An 11 year-old boy who likes to
play football and marbles and is fond of swimming like any other
children had to drop out of the school earlier this year even
though his grades usually put him among the top three students.
</P>
<P>
The problem for young Deng Xuejian was that he is
overweight. Although he comes from a poor family, he weighs 174.25
kilograms, is 1.58 meters tall, and has a 1.54 meter waist.
</P>
<P>
Deng is now receiving acupuncture treatment at a local
fat-reduction center in the northern Chinese city of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
"The boy was too fat to open his eyes, or for others to see his
neck," says Shi Lidong, a doctor at the center, "and he could
hardly walk or breathe."
</P>
<P>
Since Deng entered the center for treatment, his weight has
dropped by 15 kilograms, but doctors still don't know the reason
for the boy's weight because everything else about him is normal.
</P>
<P>
Deng says he is not afraid of the acupuncture treatment and
says that he now feels much better, and wants to go back to school
after the treatment.
</P>
<P>
Acupuncture, the traditional Chinese therapy using needles to
stimulate certain points on the body that has been used since
ancient times, is being used to curb Deng's appetite.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, acupuncture has been widely accepted by people
in many other countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
