<HEADLINE> Russian Soccer Champions Pay for Fans' Damage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Russian soccer champions
Spartak Moscow has paid about 20,000 U.S. dollars for damage
caused by fans during a September match against Real Madrid, it
was reported here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Fans destroyed 570 plastic seats in the Luzhniki sports
stadium, each worth about 15 dollars, and raided the stadium's
bathrooms.
</P>
<P>
In that match, Spartak defeated defending champions Real
Madrid 2-1 in a Champions League Group C second rotation game.
</P>
