<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Tamil Rebels kill Child Conscripts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Twenty seven Tamil rebel child
conscripts, who had tried to give themselves up to government
troops in north of Sri Lanka, were shot dead by the rebel
hierarchy Friday, according to reports reaching here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The conscripts who are from Jaffna peninsula, had been forcibly
recruited by the rebels, reports quoted security sources as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The sources said there is information to say that several of
rebel child conscripts wish to surrender to the troops. but orders
had been issued by the rebel leadership directing that severe
punishment and acts of torture be inflicted on those child
soldiers and youth conscripts, caught trying to desert the their
movement.
</P>
<P>
The rebel leadership has also warned that parents and relatives
of child soldiers who surrender themselves to the troops will also
be eliminated, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels promised UN (United Nations) Secretary General
Special Representative Olaru Ottunnu whom they met two months ago
in the Wanni jungles that they would not recruit any person below
18 to their movement which has been fighting for a separate state
in the country.
</P>
<P>
However, the sources Pointed out that the above cases clearly
indicate that this has been one of the rebels' several broken
promises which they have been making since. 
</P>
