<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Parliament Ratifies Chemical Weapons Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine's Supreme Soviet
(parliament) ratified on Friday the Chemical Weapons Convention,
which bans the design, production, accumulation and use of
chemical weapons.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax news agency reported that the ratification came
after a failed attempt of the parliament on October 6 to ratify
the convention when some parliament members feared for a possible
international control over chemical production in Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
However, this time the 450-member parliament ratified the
Convention with 285 for and 16 against.
</P>
<P>
A total of 116 countries including China, the United States,
Russia, Japan and the 15 members of the European Union, have
ratified the convention,
</P>
<P>
The Convention stipulates that severe sanctions will be imposed
on countries going against its rules. 
</P>
