<HEADLINE> Missing FIVB Cup Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The one-time missing
volleyball's women world championship cup has been found in a
faraway province in Cuba, FIVB announced here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban Volleyball Federation has localised the trophy and
sent it to the FIVB headquarters in Lausanne, the game's world
governing body said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The Cup, won by the Cubans at the last World Championship in
1994, had been brought to different provinces of the country so
that each player could present it in her hometown, and went
disappearing afterwards.
</P>
<P>
In the family house of a Cuban player, the trophy was finally
discovered, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
FIVB therefore dropped sanctions imposed on the Cuban
Federation.
</P>
<P>
The trophy, created in 1993 and weighing more than two
kilograms, will be restored and presented to the team that will
win the World Championship slated for next month in Osaka,
Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
