<DOCNO> XIE19981017.0185 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural Mothers Get Help </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 17 (Xinhua) -- More than 39,000 mostly rural
women and their loved ones have new lives and new hope thanks to
the Program of Happiness in China.
</P>
<P>
The three-year-old anti-poverty program provides loans and
assistance to impoverished women and mothers in remote and
economically backward areas of the country.
</P>
<P>
The program, co-founded in February 1995 by the China
Population Welfare Foundation, the China Family Planning
Association and the China Population News, has produced startling
results.
</P>
<P>
One of the examples is that Zhou Youcui, from southwest China's
Sichuan Province, got a 2,000 yuan (241 US dollars) low-interest
loan from the program, which enabled her to improve her life by
raising pigs and milk cows.
</P>
<P>
Formerly-indebted Zhou only had an annual income of less than
1,000 yuan (120 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Zhou has finally shrugged off poverty thanks to the program.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Daily reported that women account for 58 percent
of China's current impoverished population, which stands at 50
million-plus. They shoulder a heavy burden of production,
household chores and reproduction.
</P>
<P>
"These women's appalling living conditions, poor health and
limited educations have had a direct impact on their families and
the up-bringing of their children," said Wu Jiangchun, deputy
director o the program's organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
According to Wu, in addition to the women aided, 180,000 others
have benefited from the program's 60 million yuan (7.2 million US
dollars) investment in 24 provinces, municipalities and autonomous
regions.
</P>
<P>
The staff of the program is now working hard to achieve a goal,
by the end of this century, of helping 80,000 impoverished mothers
with the aid of more than 100 million yuan (12 million US dollars)
in funds.
</P>
<P>
The program has set up schools to educate poor mothers and to
offer them free medical treatment and regular health care
services.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday the program received 1.65 million yuan (198,700 US
dollars) in donations from home and abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
