<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Some 1,500 Bulgarians Commit Suicide Annually: Professor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Around 1,500 Bulgarians commit
suicide each year, Professor Kiril Milenkov said Friday while
presenting a national program for suicide prevention.
</P>
<P>
Suicide is most often motivated by unrequited love, but
recently suicides by bankrupt businessmen have been on the rise,
Milenkov said.
</P>
<P>
As a rule, the problems leading to suicide include unemployment,
harsh living conditions, personal and family problems, and
pressure from employers.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that women are most prone to suicide in their
teens and over 60 while men are most at risk between 40 and 60 in
connection with their professional careers.
</P>
<P>
The national program is carried out as a pilot project in
Sofia, Plovdiv, Bourgas, Dobrich and Elin Pelin.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,537 suicide attempts recorded last year in the five
areas, 365 resulted in death, according to the project director,
Lilyana Tsoneva.
</P>
<P>
The program aims at reducing the number of suicide attempts and
building an information system to record all suicide cases.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981017.0191 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northern China Province Tries to Hit Foreign Trade Growth Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province will make a
greater effort to reach this year's growth targets for foreign
trade and overseas investment, according to Vice-Governor Cai
Limin.
</P>
<P>
Hebei had 2.73 billion U.S. dollars worth of exports and
imports in the first nine months, up 3.2 percent from the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Actual overseas investment in Hebei edged down 1.2 percent on a
yearly basis to 1.02 billion U.S. dollars in the first nine
months. The negative growth rate is in sharp contrast to the
planned official annual increase of 5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Although exports has maintained growth this year, the rate has
slowed down, Cai says, and import growth has been low.
</P>
<P>
To meet this year's targets, Hebei will increase its effort to
encourage the overseas-funded enterprises to export their products
and improve the overall investment environment, Cai says, and make
an effort to improve product quality to increase competitiveness
and to enter new markets in South America, Eastern Europe, Africa,
and the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Hebei will also accelerate reforms at state-owned foreign trade
enterprises to improve their efficiency, he says.  
</P>
</TEXT>
