<HEADLINE> Motor Vehicle Sale Up in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Automobile sales in Panama
jumped 43 percent in the past 10 months this year over the same
period last year to reach 33,713 vehicles, a motor company
president said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The automobile industry had not been affected by the Asian
economic crisis, and on the contrary, there was a favorable
climate for the supply and the demand, which facilitated the
entrance of new trademarks and models into the world market,
Jorge de La Guardia said.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the increase to a number of financing policies
used by the national distributors, which allowed consumers to buy
cars at the best prices and the lowest interests.
</P>
<P>
De La Guardia explained that the top sellers in the country
were Toyota, with 8,900 autos, Mitsubishi with 6,370, followed by
Nissan, Chevrolet and Hyundai.
</P>
<P>
He said that the International Auto Fair inaugurated Friday,
which draws the participation of 83 firms from 14 countries in the
world, and the exhibition of more than 50 trademarks and 150
models of motor vehicles, would promote the sale of units in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
