<HEADLINE> Hainan-Taiwan Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Economic cooperation between
China's two island provinces, Hainan and Taiwan, has seen some
success in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Investors from Taiwan have funded more than 1,000 enterprises
in Hainan, with actual investment hitting nearly one billion U.S.
dollars. More than 250 of the firms funded by companies from
Taiwan specialize in agriculture. Hainan and Taiwan have similar
natural conditions and follow similar agricultural development
paths.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation in agricultural development between the two
provinces has good prospects, with Taiwan's capital and technology
and Hainan's land and manpower, an agronomist from Taiwan said
during a tour.
</P>
<P>
Economists here say that cooperation between the two provinces
is in the interest of various production resources.  
</P>
