<HEADLINE> Williams into Semis with Record Ace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- World number five Venus
Williams produced the fastest service recorded in women's tennis
on her way to the semi-finals at the European indoor tennis
championships in Zurich on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The American teenager's service posted 205 kph and her
opponent, Mary Pierce of France, had no choice but to fall 6-4,
6-1.
</P>
<P>
The victory set up a semi-final clash with fourth seed
Nathalie Tauziat of France and leaves Williams on track for a
final showdown with compatriot and world number one Lindsay
Davenport.
</P>
<P>
Tauziat, 31 on Saturday, needed three sets to rally for a 4-6,
7-5, 6-1 win over Austrian wild card Barbara Schett.
</P>
<P>
Newly-crowned world number one Davenport reached the last four
with a 6-3, 6-1 demolition of sixth seed Amanda Coetzer of South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
Romania's Irina Spirlea booked her place in the semi-finals
with an equally efficient 6-4, 6-0 win over eighth-seeded
Dominique Van Roost of Belgium. 
</P>
