<HEADLINE> Guivarc'h Wants to Leave Newcastle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Newcastle striker Stephane
Guivarc'h said on Friday he has been humiliated by new boss Ruud
Gullit and wants to leave St James' Park as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old, who has played just twice for Newcastle since
his 3.5 million pounds move from Auxerre in the summer, accused
the Dutchman of a lack of respect while his agent said Gullit had
"put a curse" on the World Cup-winning striker.
</P>
<P>
Guivarc'h said that he had been astonished when Gullit, who
replaced Kenny Dalglish as manager, had ordered him to train with
the reserves. "If he told me to do it again I would refuse. To
get me to train with the second team is not very classy behaviour
on his part," he added. 
