<HEADLINE> Chile Hails U.S. Interest Rates Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 16 (Xinhua) -- The 0.25 percent reduction in
the interest rates announced Thursday by the U.S. Federal Reserve
is positive, Chilean Finance Minister Eduardo Aninat said here on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
"This is a step in the right direction in relation to the
normalization of the international financial system," said the
minister.
</P>
<P>
He said that as has been pointed out by several economists,
"the world lives now in a scenario very different to the one of
1989 and 1997, and is approaching a scenario of very low
inflation, almost recessive, which must be avoided."
</P>
<P>
It is logical, he said, that in this scenario the interest
rates drop, as it occurred Thursday with the U.S. decision.
</P>
