<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Canada announced Friday that it
will extend 1.8 million Canadian dollars (1.17 million U.S.
dollars) in humanitarian aid to Russia and Ukraine this winter.
</P>
<P>
"The collapse of the rouble has driven up the prices for food,
beating fuel, clothing and transportation, bringing hardship to
hundreds of thousands of people in Russia and Ukraine," said
International Cooperation Minister Diane Marleau in a release.
</P>
<P>
