<HEADLINE> Israeli Official Meets Jordan's Hussein in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 16 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Foreign Minister
Ariel Sharon Friday met King Hussein of Jordan in Rochester,
Minnesota, where the king is being undergoing cancer treatments
since July.
</P>
<P>
Sharon praised Hussein as the Middle East's most courageous
leader, briefed and consult him on the Washington peace summit,
reports reaching here quoted officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
After the initial meeting the two went into a private
one-on-one session that was likely to last an hour.
</P>
<P>
Hussein, 62, entered the clinic on July 18. He has been
diagnosed with non-Hodgkins lymphoma, a type of cancer that
primarily afflicts the lymph nodes and spleen. He is undergoing a
series of chemotherapy treatments expected to last through
mid-November.
</P>
<P>
Israel sees Jordan as an honest partner in the Middle East
peace process.  
</P>
</TEXT>
