<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow up 117 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 16 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks rallied on Friday,
continuing to react positively to the Federal Reserve's
announcement Thursday to cut short-term interest rates, with the
Dow Jones industrial average up 117.40 points to 8416.76.
</P>
<P>
The Dow extended a 330.58 points surge on Thursday as a result
of the Fed decision to cut the discount rate and the federal funds
rate by 0.25 percent each, designed to shore up economy amid
volatile financial markets.
</P>
<P>
The Dow's rally also inspired a global stock market boom on
Friday, including Hong Kong, Singapore, Tokyo, Frankfurt and
London.
</P>
<P>
According to preliminary calculation, advancing issues led
decliners 2-1 on the New York Stock Exchange, with trading volume
soaring to 1.02 billion shares from 927 million previously.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index rose 8.93 to 1056.42, the
technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 9.94 to 1620.95, the
NYSE composite index rose 5.78 to 522.24 and the American Stock
Exchange composite index rose 5.84 to 604.50. 
</P>
</TEXT>
